  "texts": [
    "That allowed the importance sampling method called V-trace to scale to data distributions over which its original formulation would become unstable.",
    "V-trace is a technique widely used in training actor-critic agents, which controls the variance commonly observed in naive importance sampling, but at the cost of introducing bias in the estimates.",
    "This bias is because its estimate of the v π value function does not correspond to the expected return value for the policy π but rather for a policy π, which is only implicitly related to π and computed biased.",
    "Therefore, it can distance too much from π.",
    "In this way, the policy gradi- ent is also biased so that, given a value function v *, the V-trace does not guarantee conver- gence to a policy π * in off-line training, as the authors demonstrated."
